    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>IOTA Notarization for VeriPura</h1>
            <p>Comprehensive Guide to Blockchain-Based Document Verification</p>
        </header>
        
        <div class="content">
            <h2>Core Functionality</h2>
            
            <div class="functionality-box">
                <h3>What is IOTA Notarization?</h3>
                <p>IOTA Notarization creates tamper-proof, timestamped records of digital assets on IOTA's Tangle network. It generates cryptographic proof that a document or data existed at a specific moment in time, enabling verification without revealing the actual content.</p>
            </div>
            
            <h3>How It Works</h3>
            <ol style="margin-left: 40px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;"><strong>Hash the document/data</strong> - Creates a unique digital fingerprint</li>
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;"><strong>Submit hash to IOTA network</strong> - Records it with timestamp</li>
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;"><strong>Receive immutable proof</strong> - Get cryptographic evidence of existence</li>
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;"><strong>Enable verification</strong> - Anyone can verify authenticity using the hash</li>
            </ol>
            
            <div class="benefits">
                <h4>Key Advantages Over Traditional Notarization</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Instant:</strong> Seconds instead of days or weeks</li>
                    <li><strong>Global:</strong> Accessible from anywhere in the world</li>
                    <li><strong>Feeless:</strong> Critical for high-volume notarization (IOTA's unique advantage)</li>
                    <li><strong>No intermediaries:</strong> Direct cryptographic verification</li>
                    <li><strong>Cryptographically secure:</strong> Mathematically proven authenticity</li>
                    <li><strong>Cost-effective at scale:</strong> Ideal for enterprise applications</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h2>VeriPura-Specific Applications</h2>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3><span class="use-case-number">1</span>Health Certificate Notarization</h3>
                <h4>Problem:</h4>
                <p>Health certificates can be forged or disputed. EU customs has no quick way to verify authenticity without contacting the issuing authority, which can take days.</p>
                
                <h4>VeriPura Solution:</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <li>Exporting country's health authority notarizes certificate at issuance</li>
                    <li>Importer uploads cert to VeriPura → instant verification against notarized hash</li>
                    <li>EU customs scans QR code → sees cryptographic proof of authenticity</li>
                    <li>No need to contact issuing authority (saves days)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="transaction-flow">
                    <strong>Transaction Flow:</strong><br>
                    • 1 notarization per certificate at issuance<br>
                    • Multiple verification queries (importer, freight forwarder, customs)<br>
                    • ~5-10 transactions per shipment
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3><span class="use-case-number">2</span>Phytosanitary Certificate Chain of Custody</h3>
                <h4>Problem:</h4>
                <p>Phyto certificates change hands multiple times (inspector → ministry → exporter → importer). Questions about authenticity arise at each transfer point.</p>
                
                <h4>VeriPura Solution:</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <li>Each handoff notarized with timestamp</li>
                    <li>Creates auditable chain showing certificate never left proper custody</li>
                    <li>Detects if certificate was altered after initial issuance</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="transaction-flow">
                    <strong>Transaction Flow:</strong><br>
                    • Initial issuance: 1 notarization<br>
                    • Each transfer: 1 notarization<br>
                    • ~4-6 transactions per certificate lifecycle
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3><span class="use-case-number">3</span>Pesticide Residue Test Results</h3>
                <h4>Problem:</h4>
                <p>Lab test results can be backdated or falsified. Importers can't verify when tests were actually conducted.</p>
                
                <h4>VeriPura Solution:</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <li>Laboratory notarizes test results immediately upon completion</li>
                    <li>Timestamp proves results aren't from old batch</li>
                    <li>VeriPura automatically checks if test is <30 days old (EU requirement)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="transaction-flow">
                    <strong>Transaction Flow:</strong><br>
                    • 1 notarization per lab test<br>
                    • Verification queries as needed<br>
                    • High volume (every produce shipment requires testing)
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3><span class="use-case-number">4</span>Certificate of Origin Validation</h3>
                <h4>Problem:</h4>
                <p>Preferential tariff treatment requires proof of origin. Certificate fraud is common, costing importers money in denied tariff benefits.</p>
                
                <h4>VeriPura Solution:</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <li>Chamber of Commerce notarizes certificate issuance</li>
                    <li>Importer proves origin for tariff benefits without re-verification</li>
                    <li>Customs can audit trail back to issuing authority</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="transaction-flow">
                    <strong>Transaction Flow:</strong><br>
                    • 1 notarization per certificate<br>
                    • Multiple customs queries<br>
                    • ~3-5 transactions per shipment
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3><span class="use-case-number">5</span>Document Revocation Registry</h3>
                <h4>Problem:</h4>
                <p>If a health authority discovers contamination post-certification, they revoke the certificate—but the importer may not know until cargo is rejected at the border, resulting in massive losses.</p>
                
                <h4>VeriPura Solution:</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <li>Initial certificate: notarized</li>
                    <li>Revocation: new notarization with "REVOKED" status + reason</li>
                    <li>VeriPura checks revocation status before shipment departs</li>
                    <li>Real-time alerts to importer if certificate revoked</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="transaction-flow">
                    <strong>Transaction Flow:</strong><br>
                    • 1 notarization per revocation event<br>
                    • Continuous monitoring queries by VeriPura<br>
                    • Prevents costly shipping of rejected cargo
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3><span class="use-case-number">6</span>Invoice-Packing List-Certificate Reconciliation</h3>
                <h4>Problem:</h4>
                <p>EU customs requires invoice, packing list, and health certificate to match exactly. Discrepancies cause delays and potential rejection.</p>
                
                <h4>VeriPura Solution:</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <li>Notarize all three documents with cross-references</li>
                    <li>VeriPura automatically checks: quantities match, dates align, products consistent</li>
                    <li>Flags mismatches before shipment departs</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="transaction-flow">
                    <strong>Transaction Flow:</strong><br>
                    • 3 notarizations per shipment (invoice + packing list + certificate)<br>
                    • Automated reconciliation queries<br>
                    • ~5-8 transactions per shipment
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <h2>Immutable vs. Versioned Documents</h2>
            
            <h3>Two Approaches to Document Management</h3>
            
            <table class="comparison-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Feature</th>
                        <th>Immutable Notarization</th>
                        <th>Versioned Document Chain</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>How it works</strong></td>
                        <td>Document hashed once and frozen at that moment</td>
                        <td>Each version notarized with links to previous versions</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>When changes occur</strong></td>
                        <td>New hash = proof document was altered</td>
                        <td>Creates auditable chain showing what changed</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Best for</strong></td>
                        <td>Final certificates, lab results, regulatory submissions</td>
                        <td>Drafts, workflows, multi-authority approvals</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Verification</strong></td>
                        <td>Match/no match against original hash</td>
                        <td>Complete history of all changes with reasons</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Use case example</strong></td>
                        <td>Final approved health certificate</td>
                        <td>Certificate going through approval stages</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            
            <div class="functionality-box">
                <h3>Certificate Amendment Tracking Example</h3>
                <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> Health certificate issued, but exporter realizes product description contains typo. Authority issues amendment.</p>
                
                <div class="code-block">
Version 1 (Original):
- Issued: Jan 15, 2026
- Product: "Frozen shrimp" 
- Hash: abc123...
- Status: "Issued"

Version 2 (Amended):
- Issued: Jan 17, 2026
- Product: "Frozen prawns" (corrected)
- Hash: def456...
- Previous: abc123...
- Change: "Product name correction - no material change"
- Status: "Amended"
                </div>
                
                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>VeriPura Validation:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                    <li>Check if amendment was authorized (health authority DID)</li>
                    <li>Verify amendment reason is acceptable (typo vs. substantive change)</li>
                    <li>Alert importer to review amendment</li>
                    <li>EU customs sees complete history</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h2>Strategic Advantages for VeriPura</h2>
            
            <h3>vs. Traditional Blockchain</h3>
            <div class="benefits">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Feeless:</strong> Can notarize every minor event without cost constraints</li>
                    <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> Handles high transaction volumes (thousands of shipments daily)</li>
                    <li><strong>Speed:</strong> Instant notarization (critical for time-sensitive certifications)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h3>vs. Centralized Database</h3>
            <div class="benefits">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Trust-minimized:</strong> No single party controls the record</li>
                    <li><strong>Globally verifiable:</strong> Anyone can verify without VeriPura as intermediary</li>
                    <li><strong>Regulatory compliance:</strong> Immutable audit trails for EU regulations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Business Model Implications</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 40px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Can offer "freemium" notarization (low marginal cost)</li>
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Premium features: automated monitoring, revocation alerts, reconciliation</li>
                <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Network effects: More notarized documents = more valuable verification service</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Implementation Roadmap</h2>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Phase 1 (Immediate)</h3>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                    <li>Health certificate notarization</li>
                    <li>Certificate of origin validation</li>
                    <li>Document revocation registry</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Phase 2 (3-6 months)</h3>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                    <li>Phytosanitary certificate chain of custody</li>
                    <li>Lab test result timestamping</li>
                    <li>Invoice-packing list-certificate reconciliation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Phase 3 (Future)</h3>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
                    <li>Multi-language document integrity</li>
                    <li>Exporter self-audit trails</li>
                    <li>Smart contract enforcement for workflows</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
